						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar lying in the compound of the ruined Īśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Rājakēsarivarman (Sundarachōḷa) 7: 964 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription on the grounds of palaeography may be assigned to the tenth century A.D., as it may belong to the reign-period of Rājakēsarivarmaṉ Sundarachōḷa.</p>						

						<p>It records the definition of the boundaries of a plot of land, 1/8 of a <hi rend="italic">vēli</hi> in extent, belonging to the god who was pleased to keep standing. Among the boundaries of the land two plots of <hi rend="italic">strīdhana</hi> land owned by the wife of Sāvāndi Śrīkaṇṭaṉ, is mentioned.</p>						

						</summary>
